{
  "stem": "13457.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was initially very angry, angry at Jews, that they didn't tell me, in Israel, the extent of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In other words, they didn't spell it out for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In our family, my parents were heartbroken.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They obviously understood it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But nobody yet-- nobody could yet put it in words or in numbers, or in attitudes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It is just that there was some-- when my father got old-- there was some woman coming, taking care of him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she was telling the story to my mother that they were leading them to the ditches to be shot.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she heard the shooting, and she just escaped.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I-- I was, in 1946-- in other words, before Israel, I came to.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But after the war already, after '45, I was with somebody on a kibbutz, that he was telling the story, that how the Germans were evacuating their concentration camps towards the end of the war, and how he survived that.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "At that time, I was 16.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my perception was, well, that was his tough luck that he was where-- where he was.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And had he been here in Israel, as I was, then it wouldn't have happened to him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I couldn't quite understand the mechanics of it, the mechanics, that I started to pick up the full understanding of Holocaust only on my own, when I was fully grown up, already with children.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I would go into every detail of every locality, every date in-- in-- in Warsaw, as a place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I would go into details how different members of my family perished.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[CRYING] Um, to be-- to be specific, for instance-- and then, when my older son, I think, had bar mitzvah, and the whole [NON-ENGLISH] came.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They from Sweden.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They came from Denmark.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
